# AddProject.skill

Repo-local shortcut for the portfolio import SOP.

Canonical skill:

```text
skills/add-project/SKILL.md
```

Use it by saying:

```text
使用 AddProject.skill，把 D:\path\to\project-materials 整理成作品集新项目。
```

The skill covers the full path from a user-provided raw project folder to website-ready portfolio content:

1. inspect the repo and environment;
2. read the project operating docs;
3. create an import branch;
4. scan the source folder read-only;
5. classify public, private, reference-only, and needs-confirmation materials;
6. copy and normalize public-safe uploads;
7. use `skills/engineering-note-writer/SKILL.md` when turning rough bullet points into engineering-note prose;
8. create or update bilingual project pages, notes, and media entries;
9. preview and review the website;
10. run validation, typecheck, build, and audit;
11. commit, push, and optionally merge/release after user approval;
12. update durable memory/docs when the public portfolio state changes.

Hard gate: before copying files, writing content, verifying, committing, or releasing, use:

```text
skills/add-project/references/hard-gated-checklist.md
```

Important: `public/uploads/` is public internet. The skill must not publish sensitive files merely because they are unlinked.
